1. What LCES Is (In One Sentence)

LCES is a procedural‑literacy system that teaches users how to build structured, review‑ready legal records under real‑world constraints.

Two representative lines from your document anchor this:

“The record is the case.”
“If it is not structured, preserved, and sequenced correctly, it does not exist on review.”

This is the conceptual north star.

---

1. What LCES Helps You Do

Users learn to:

- build decision‑ready records
• control framing
• preserve reviewable issues
• expose procedural breakdowns
• enforce discipline under constraint
• avoid common failure modes (no proposed order, no archive, narrative overload)

This is the practical value proposition.

